         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Continuous Measure"},{"id":"b","text":"Discrete Dimension"},{"id":"c","text":"Continuous Dimension"},{"id":"d","text":"Discrete Measure"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$In Tableau, blue pills represent discrete fields — typically dimensions (qualitative, categorical). Green pills represent continuous fields — typically measures. While dimensions can be made continuous and measures can be made discrete, the default blue pill represents a Discrete Dimension. Per the source: 'Dimensions (qualitative, blue pill): typically discrete.'$patch$, $patch$Connect to and Transform Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/datafields_typesandroles_dataroles.htm","label":"Tableau – Dimensions and Measures, Blue and Green"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
