  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau developer wants to schedule a Tableau Prep flow to run automatically on a recurring basis without manual execution. Which Tableau product component enables this scheduling capability?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Tableau Desktop"},{"id":"b","text":"Tableau Reader"},{"id":"c","text":"Prep Conductor (on Tableau Server or Tableau Cloud)"},{"id":"d","text":"Tableau Public"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Per the source material, 'Tableau Prep flows can be scheduled on Tableau Server / Cloud via Prep Conductor.' Prep Conductor is the component responsible for automating flow execution on a schedule. Tableau Desktop is an authoring tool and cannot schedule flows. Tableau Reader is a free viewer for packaged workbooks. Tableau Public is a free public-sharing platform with no scheduling capability for Prep flows.$patch$, $patch$Connect to and Transform Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/server/en-us/prep_conductor_schedule_flow_task.htm","label":"Tableau – Schedule Flow Tasks with Prep Conductor"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
