  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$In Tableau Desktop, which data type would be assigned by default to a field containing values such as TRUE and FALSE?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"String (Abc)"},{"id":"b","text":"Number (#)"},{"id":"c","text":"Boolean (T/F)"},{"id":"d","text":"Date"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Per the source material, the Boolean data type (represented as T/F) is the appropriate type for fields containing TRUE and FALSE values. Tableau will automatically detect and assign the Boolean type when connecting to such a field. String (Abc) stores text, Number (#) stores numeric values, and Date stores calendar date values — none of which match a true/false binary field.$patch$, $patch$Connect to and Transform Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/datafields_typesandroles_datatypes.htm","label":"Tableau – Data Types in Tableau"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
