         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Dimension filters"},{"id":"b","text":"Measure filters"},{"id":"c","text":"Context filters"},{"id":"d","text":"INCLUDE LOD expressions"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$According to the source, the order of operations is: 'Extract filters → Data source filters → Context filters → FIXED LODs → Dimension filters → INCLUDE/EXCLUDE LODs → Measure filters → Table calcs.' Context filters are evaluated before FIXED LODs, which means making a filter a context filter allows it to restrict the data seen by FIXED expressions. Dimension filters, measure filters, and INCLUDE/EXCLUDE LODs are all evaluated after FIXED LODs.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/order_of_operations.htm","label":"Tableau – Order of Operations (Order of Filters)"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
