         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"A continuous date field"},{"id":"b","text":"A dimension string field such as Region"},{"id":"c","text":"A binned measure field (e.g., Order Quantity (bin))"},{"id":"d","text":"A calculated table calculation"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material defines a histogram as showing 'distribution of a single measure via bins.' Tableau creates a histogram by binning a numeric measure; the resulting bin field is placed on Columns (treated as a dimension) with a count measure on Rows. A date field produces time series, a string dimension produces bar charts, and a table calculation does not create bins.$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
