         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Tableau Bridge and embedded credentials"},{"id":"b","text":"Tableau Prep Conductor and a scheduled extract refresh"},{"id":"c","text":"Tableau Catalog and a data quality warning"},{"id":"d","text":"A connected app and JWT authentication"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states: 'Tableau Bridge: keeps Tableau Cloud connected to on-prem data sources (private networks)' and separately notes that when publishing you can 'embed credentials for live connections.' Together, Tableau Bridge provides the network tunnel from Tableau Cloud to the private on-premises SQL Server, while embedding credentials removes the prompt for end-users. Tableau Prep Conductor (B) schedules flows, not live connections. Tableau Catalog (C) manages metadata and lineage but does not maintain live connectivity. Connected apps/JWT (D) are for embedded viewing authentication, not for data-source connectivity.$patch$, $patch$Publish and Manage Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/online/en-us/qs_refresh_local_data.htm","label":"Tableau Bridge Overview – Tableau Help"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/publish_datasources.htm","label":"Publish a Data Source – Tableau Help"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
