INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$On a Tableau Server site, a project's permissions have been configured with a specific capability set for a group. A workbook is then published into that project without any workbook-level permissions being explicitly set. What governs the effective permissions on that workbook for the group?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The site role of each individual user in the group, which always takes precedence over project-level settings"},{"id":"b","text":"The workbook inherits the permissions from the project, because no workbook-level override has been set"},{"id":"c","text":"The workbook defaults to the 'None' permission template until an admin explicitly grants access"},{"id":"d","text":"The workbook automatically grants all capabilities to Creators and denies all capabilities to Viewers regardless of project settings"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material explicitly states: 'Inherited permissions from project unless overridden.' Because no workbook-level permissions were set at publish time, the workbook inherits whatever capability set was defined at the project level for that group. Option A is partially true (site roles set an upper bound) but the question asks what governs effective permissions on the workbook in this scenario—that is project inheritance. Option C is incorrect; there is no automatic 'None' default for published content when project permissions exist. Option D describes a hardcoded behavior that does not exist in Tableau's permissions model.$patch$, $patch$Publish and Manage Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/server/en-us/permissions.htm","label":"Permissions – Tableau Help"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/server/en-us/projects.htm","label":"Manage Permissions for Projects – Tableau Help"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
