  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A business analyst needs to be automatically notified by email whenever the daily revenue measure in a published Tableau dashboard drops below $50,000, without requiring them to log in and check the view manually. Which Tableau Server/Cloud feature should the analyst use?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Subscription"},{"id":"b","text":"Scheduled extract refresh"},{"id":"c","text":"Data-driven alert"},{"id":"d","text":"Tableau Pulse digest"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material defines a data-driven alert as: 'notify when a measure crosses a threshold on a view.' This is precisely the use case—automated email notification triggered by a measure breaching a defined threshold. A Subscription (A) sends scheduled email snapshots of a dashboard on a time-based schedule, not when a specific value is crossed. A scheduled extract refresh (B) updates the underlying data but does not send threshold-based alerts. Tableau Pulse (D) provides AI-driven personalized insights and digests but is not specifically configured around a user-defined numeric threshold trigger.$patch$, $patch$Publish and Manage Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/data_alerts.htm","label":"Data-Driven Alerts – Tableau Help"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/subscribe_workspace.htm","label":"Subscriptions – Tableau Help"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
