INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau Site Administrator needs to embed a published dashboard into an internal company web portal and ensure that users are authenticated without being prompted to log in to Tableau separately. According to Tableau best practices, which authentication mechanism is designed for this embedded scenario?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Embedding the dashboard in an iframe with no additional authentication configuration"},{"id":"b","text":"Using Connected Apps with JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication"},{"id":"c","text":"Configuring a data-driven alert with a shared service account"},{"id":"d","text":"Enabling Tableau Catalog lineage on the embedded data source"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states: 'Connected apps / JWT auth for embedded viewing.' Connected Apps with JWT allow the hosting web application to generate a signed token that Tableau trusts, providing seamless single-sign-on for embedded content without a separate Tableau login prompt. Option A (plain iframe) will work for rendering but does not handle authentication—users would still be prompted to log in. Option C (data-driven alert) is for threshold notifications and has no bearing on embedded authentication. Option D (Catalog lineage) is a metadata discovery feature unrelated to embedding authentication.$patch$, $patch$Publish and Manage Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/server/en-us/connected_apps.htm","label":"Connected Apps – Tableau Help"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/api/embedding_api/en-us/index.html","label":"Tableau Embedding API v3 Overview"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
