  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A data governance team wants to flag a published data source on Tableau Server as unreliable because the underlying data pipeline has a known issue. They want anyone who opens a workbook connected to that data source to see a visible warning. Which Tableau feature enables this?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Assigning the 'None' permission template to the data source"},{"id":"b","text":"Setting a data quality warning on the data source via Tableau Catalog"},{"id":"c","text":"Removing the extract refresh schedule for the data source"},{"id":"d","text":"Revoking the 'Download' capability from all users on the data source"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material describes Tableau Catalog (part of the Data Management add-on) as providing: 'Data quality warnings on data sources.' A data quality warning visibly surfaces to any user opening a workbook connected to the flagged data source, serving as an in-product governance signal. Option A (setting 'None' permissions) restricts access but does not communicate data quality issues. Option C (removing the schedule) stops data refreshes but provides no visible warning to consumers. Option D (revoking Download) limits what users can do with the data but does not surface a quality warning.$patch$, $patch$Publish and Manage Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/server/en-us/dm_dqw.htm","label":"Data Quality Warnings – Tableau Help"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/server/en-us/dm_catalog_overview.htm","label":"Tableau Catalog Overview – Tableau Help"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
