  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$When publishing a workbook from Tableau Desktop to Tableau Server using Server > Publish Workbook, which of the following correctly describes the difference between Tableau Cloud and Tableau Server regarding their hosting model?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Tableau Cloud is self-hosted on the customer's own hardware or cloud VM, while Tableau Server is a SaaS offering managed by Salesforce."},{"id":"b","text":"Tableau Cloud is a SaaS-hosted offering managed by Salesforce/Tableau, while Tableau Server is self-hosted on-premises or on a cloud VM managed by the customer."},{"id":"c","text":"Tableau Cloud and Tableau Server are identical in deployment model but differ only in the number of supported users."},{"id":"d","text":"Tableau Server is exclusively deployed in public cloud environments, while Tableau Cloud can also be installed on-premises."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material explicitly states: 'Tableau Cloud = SaaS-hosted; Tableau Server = self-hosted on-prem or cloud VM.' Option B matches this definition precisely. Option A reverses the two definitions. Option C is incorrect; the hosting model is a fundamental architectural difference, not merely a user-count difference. Option D inverts the definitions—Tableau Server can be on-premises or on customer-managed cloud VMs, and Tableau Cloud is the fully managed SaaS product, not an on-premises option.$patch$, $patch$Publish and Manage Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/online/en-us/what_is_tableau_online.htm","label":"What is Tableau Cloud? – Tableau Help"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/server/en-us/get_started_server_admin.htm","label":"Tableau Server Overview – Tableau Help"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
