         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"After Dimension filters"},{"id":"b","text":"Before Context filters"},{"id":"c","text":"After Context filters but before Dimension filters"},{"id":"d","text":"After Measure filters"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$According to the source material, the Tableau order of operations is: 'Extract filters → Data source filters → Context filters → FIXED LODs → Dimension filters → INCLUDE/EXCLUDE LODs → Measure filters → Table calcs.' FIXED LODs are evaluated after Context filters but before Dimension filters, which means a Dimension filter on [Category] will NOT affect the FIXED LOD result unless that filter is promoted to a Context filter.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/order_of_operations.htm","label":"Tableau Order of Operations"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
