         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Running Total"},{"id":"b","text":"Percent of Total"},{"id":"c","text":"Percent Difference"},{"id":"d","text":"Moving Average"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Percent of Total expresses each cell's value as a percentage of a subtotal or grand total, which is exactly what is needed to show each quarter's contribution to annual sales. Running Total accumulates values cumulatively. Percent Difference shows the relative change versus a reference cell. Moving Average smooths values over a window of rows. The source states: 'Percent of total: each cell as % of subtotal or grand total.'$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/calculations_tablecalculations_quick.htm","label":"Tableau Quick Table Calculations"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
