  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau analyst wants to compare actual sales performance against a quarterly target, also showing acceptable performance bands (poor, satisfactory, good). Which chart type is BEST suited for this requirement?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Bar chart"},{"id":"b","text":"Bullet chart"},{"id":"c","text":"Box plot"},{"id":"d","text":"Waterfall chart"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material explicitly states: 'Bullet chart: actual vs target with reference bands.' A bullet chart is purpose-built to show a primary measure (actual sales) against a target marker and qualitative performance bands (poor, satisfactory, good). A bar chart only shows categorical comparisons without target/band encoding. A box plot shows distribution with quartiles and outliers — not target comparison. A waterfall chart shows cumulative additions and subtractions over a sequence, not actual-vs-target.$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/qs_bullet_graphs.htm","label":"Tableau — Build a Bullet Graph"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
