         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Color"},{"id":"b","text":"Shape"},{"id":"c","text":"Detail"},{"id":"d","text":"Path"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material defines the Detail mark as: 'split marks without other visual encoding.' Placing a dimension on Detail increases mark granularity (disaggregates the data) without changing any visible attribute. Color would visually encode the dimension with hue. Shape would assign distinct icons to dimension members. Path connects marks in a specific order (e.g., by date) and is typically used on line or polygon mark types.$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/buildmanual_shelves_marks.htm","label":"Tableau — Marks Card Reference"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
