  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$Which Tableau feature allows an analyst to dynamically replace one measure with another in a visualization without editing the underlying worksheet?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Parameter with a calculated field referencing the parameter"},{"id":"b","text":"Sets used as a filter"},{"id":"c","text":"Groups applied to the measure field"},{"id":"d","text":"Context filter applied to the measure"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A parameter can hold a user-selectable value (e.g., 'Sales', 'Profit', 'Quantity'). A calculated field using a CASE or IF statement referencing the parameter then returns the correct measure dynamically. This is the standard pattern for dynamic measure selection in Tableau. Sets are typically used for grouping dimensions into in/out buckets. Groups consolidate dimension members. Context filters change filter evaluation order but do not swap measures.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/parameters_create.htm","label":"Tableau – Create and Edit Parameters"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
