  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A user wants to find which individual customers are both in the top 10 by Revenue AND in the bottom 10 by Profit Margin. Which Tableau feature is BEST suited to identify this combined segment?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Combined sets using the intersection of two separate sets"},{"id":"b","text":"A single Top N filter applied to Revenue"},{"id":"c","text":"A context filter on Profit Margin"},{"id":"d","text":"A quick table calculation for running total"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Tableau Sets can be created for top/bottom conditions. Two sets can then be combined using set intersection to find members that satisfy both conditions simultaneously. A single Top N filter only addresses one metric. A context filter changes evaluation order but cannot natively intersect two ranked conditions. Table calculations do not segment members across two independent ranking criteria.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/sortgroup_sets_create.htm","label":"Tableau – Create Sets"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/sortgroup_sets_combined.htm","label":"Tableau – Combine Sets"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
