  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An analyst wants to show the percentage contribution of each product sub-category to total sales within the same visualization row. Which Table Calculation setting in Tableau achieves this?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Percent of Total computed using Table (across)"},{"id":"b","text":"Percent of Total computed using Table (down)"},{"id":"c","text":"Running Total computed using Table (across)"},{"id":"d","text":"Percent Difference From computed using Pane (across)"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Percent of Total with the addressing set to Table (across) calculates each cell's value as a percentage of the total of all cells in the same row (across columns), which is the correct way to show each sub-category's share within the row. Table (down) would compute percentage down the column, not across. Running Total accumulates rather than computing share. Percent Difference From measures change relative to a reference point, not contribution to total.$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/calculations_tablecalculations.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Table Calculations"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/calculations_tablecalculations_typesoverview.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Percent of Total Table Calculation"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
