  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$When building a Gantt chart in Tableau to show project task durations, which measure encoding is used to represent each task's length along the time axis?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The duration measure is placed on the Size shelf"},{"id":"b","text":"The duration measure is placed on the Columns shelf as a second date field"},{"id":"c","text":"The duration measure is placed on the Rows shelf alongside the task dimension"},{"id":"d","text":"The duration measure is placed on the Detail shelf so Tableau auto-sizes each bar"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$In a Tableau Gantt chart, the mark type is set to Gantt Bar. The start date goes on Columns, the task/category goes on Rows, and the duration (a numeric measure representing the number of days or other units) is placed on the Size shelf to stretch each bar to the correct length. Placing duration on Columns creates a second axis. Placing it on Rows disrupts the layout. Placing it on Detail does not size the bars.$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/buildexamples_gantt.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Build a Gantt Chart"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
