         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Right-click one of the axes and select 'Synchronize Axis'"},{"id":"b","text":"Right-click the view and select 'Fit Width'"},{"id":"c","text":"Drag both measures to the Columns shelf instead of the Rows shelf"},{"id":"d","text":"Set both axes to a fixed range of 0 to the maximum value in the Format pane"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$After creating a dual-axis chart, the two axes may have different scales. 'Synchronize Axis' aligns the scales of both axes so that they share the same zero baseline and proportional scale. 'Fit Width' is a view sizing option unrelated to axis alignment. Moving measures to Columns changes the chart orientation. Manually setting fixed ranges is tedious and breaks when data changes.$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
