         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Edit the filter and choose 'Apply to Worksheets → All Using This Data Source'"},{"id":"b","text":"Right-click the dashboard and select 'Synchronize Filters'"},{"id":"c","text":"Create a parameter and link it to all worksheets manually"},{"id":"d","text":"Place the filter in the dashboard's global filter tray by dragging it to the layout container"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The 'Apply to Worksheets → All Using This Data Source' option on a filter makes that filter a global filter applied to every sheet in the workbook that uses the same data source, including all sheets on the dashboard. Option B ('Synchronize Filters') does not exist as a right-click dashboard option. Parameters (C) require manual wiring and calculated fields. Tableau does not have a 'global filter tray' that works by drag-and-drop (D).$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
