  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$Which chart type in Tableau is most appropriate for visualizing the statistical distribution of a continuous measure across multiple categories, including median, quartiles, and outliers, without creating a custom calculation?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Box-and-Whisker Plot (Box Plot)"},{"id":"b","text":"Histogram"},{"id":"c","text":"Area Chart"},{"id":"d","text":"Scatter Plot"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A Box-and-Whisker Plot natively displays the median, interquartile range (Q1–Q3), whiskers extending to 1.5× IQR, and individual outlier points for each category dimension—all without custom calculations. A Histogram shows distribution as bins for a single measure and cannot easily compare across multiple categories. An Area Chart shows cumulative or sequential data over time. A Scatter Plot shows the relationship between two measures, not distribution statistics.$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/buildexamples_boxplot.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Build a Box Plot"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
