  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$In Tableau Desktop, what is the primary purpose of a Parameter Action on a dashboard?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"It allows a user's click or hover on a mark to dynamically change the value of a parameter, which can then drive calculations, filters, or reference lines across worksheets"},{"id":"b","text":"It creates an animated transition between dashboard pages when the user clicks a navigation button"},{"id":"c","text":"It enables a parameter to be published to Tableau Server so all users share the same parameter value"},{"id":"d","text":"It automatically refreshes the data source extract whenever a parameter value changes"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Parameter Actions (introduced in Tableau 2019.2) let users interact with marks (via click, hover, or menu) to update a parameter's value in real time. Because parameters can feed into calculated fields, filters, and reference lines, this creates highly interactive dashboards. Options B, C, and D describe features that do not exist or are unrelated to Parameter Actions—animated page transitions are not a native Tableau feature, parameters are not 'published' with shared values across users in this manner, and parameter changes do not trigger extract refreshes.$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/actions_parameters.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Parameter Actions"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
