  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An analyst creates a calculated field using a FIXED Level of Detail (LOD) expression: { FIXED [Region] : SUM([Sales]) }. When this field is placed in a view that also includes [Category], what does the calculated field return for each mark?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The total Sales for the Region of that mark, regardless of the Category dimension in the view"},{"id":"b","text":"The total Sales for the specific Region and Category combination of that mark"},{"id":"c","text":"The grand total Sales across all Regions and Categories"},{"id":"d","text":"An error, because LOD expressions cannot be used in views that contain additional dimensions"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A FIXED LOD expression computes its aggregate at the declared dimension level only—in this case [Region]—and ignores any other dimensions present in the view (like [Category]). Every mark belonging to the same Region will show the same SUM([Sales]) value for that Region regardless of Category. INCLUDE or EXCLUDE LOD expressions are sensitive to view dimensions; FIXED is not. No error occurs—FIXED LOD expressions coexist freely with additional view dimensions.$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/calculations_calculatedfields_lod.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Level of Detail Expressions"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/calculations_calculatedfields_lod_fixed.htm","label":"Tableau Help – FIXED LOD Expressions"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
