  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau developer wants to highlight only the marks in a scatter plot that meet a specific condition—for example, orders where Profit Ratio is below –10%—while keeping all other marks visible but de-emphasized. Which Tableau feature is designed specifically for this purpose?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Highlighter (using a calculated boolean field as the highlight target)"},{"id":"b","text":"A standard dimension filter that keeps only the qualifying marks"},{"id":"c","text":"Reference Band set between –10% and the minimum value"},{"id":"d","text":"A Set created from the condition and placed on the Color shelf"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["d"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Placing a Set (created with the condition Profit Ratio < –10%) on the Color shelf is the most direct and purpose-built approach: Tableau automatically colors In/Out members differently, highlighting qualifying marks while keeping all other marks visible. A standard filter (B) removes non-qualifying marks entirely. A Highlighter (A) is triggered interactively by the user, not by a calculated condition, and does not de-emphasize rather than remove marks programmatically. A Reference Band (C) draws a shaded region on the axis but does not re-color individual marks.$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/sortgroup_sets_create.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Create Sets"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/actions_highlight.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Highlight Marks in the View"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
