  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$When creating a tooltip in Tableau, an analyst wants to embed a live mini-chart that updates based on which mark the user hovers over. Which Tableau feature enables this?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Viz in Tooltip, by inserting a sheet reference inside the Tooltip editor"},{"id":"b","text":"A floating image container placed over the main worksheet"},{"id":"c","text":"A dashboard URL action that opens a separate browser window"},{"id":"d","text":"A custom JavaScript extension added to the tooltip HTML field"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Viz in Tooltip (available since Tableau 10.5) allows analysts to reference another worksheet inside the Tooltip editor using the Insert Sheet button. When a user hovers over a mark, the referenced worksheet renders filtered to the context of that mark, providing a live, contextual mini-visualization. A floating image container is static. A URL action navigates to a URL in a browser. Tableau tooltips do not support custom JavaScript in Desktop.$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
