  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau analyst is building a text table (crosstab) that shows quarterly sales. They want the cell values to display as the percent change compared to the previous quarter within each row. Which Table Calculation type and direction setting should be applied to the Sales measure?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Percent Difference From, computed using Table (across), relative to Previous"},{"id":"b","text":"Percent of Total, computed using Table (across)"},{"id":"c","text":"Running Total, computed using Table (across), with a Percent number format"},{"id":"d","text":"Difference From, computed using Table (down), relative to First"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Percent Difference From calculates the percentage change of each value relative to a reference value—in this case 'Previous' (the preceding cell). Setting the computation to Table (across) ensures it moves quarter by quarter within each row. This directly yields period-over-period percent change. Percent of Total (B) shows each cell's share of the row total, not change. Running Total (C) accumulates values and a percent format does not convert it to percent change. Difference From (D) returns an absolute difference, not a percentage, and computing down the table moves across rows rather than across quarters.$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/calculations_tablecalculations_typesoverview.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Percent Difference Table Calculation"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/calculations_tablecalculations.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Table Calculation Types"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
