  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau Desktop author has finished building a workbook and wants to publish it to Tableau Server so that other users in the organization can view it. Which built-in permission role on Tableau Server grants a user the ability to VIEW published workbooks but explicitly prevents them from downloading or saving a local copy?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Viewer"},{"id":"b","text":"Explorer"},{"id":"c","text":"Creator"},{"id":"d","text":"Site Administrator Explorer"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The Viewer role is designed for users who only need to consume published content. Viewers can interact with views (apply filters, use tooltips) but cannot download workbooks or connect to underlying data sources, preventing local copies. Explorer and Creator roles grant progressively more capabilities, including the ability to download workbooks. Site Administrator Explorer has broad administrative rights. The Viewer role is therefore the most restrictive option that still allows viewing published content.$patch$, $patch$Publish and Manage Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/server/en-us/permissions.htm","label":"Tableau Server Roles and Permissions"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/server/en-us/users_site_roles.htm","label":"Tableau Site Roles Overview"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
