INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau Server administrator wants to organize content so that the Marketing team's workbooks are isolated from the Finance team's workbooks, each with their own set of users and permissions. Which Tableau Server structural element is the correct tool for this separation?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Projects"},{"id":"b","text":"Collections"},{"id":"c","text":"Workbook Folders"},{"id":"d","text":"Separate Tableau Desktop installations"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Projects are the primary organizational and permission-boundary containers on Tableau Server and Tableau Cloud. Administrators can assign different permission rules to different projects, effectively isolating team content. Collections (option b) are a Tableau Cloud feature for curating content across projects but do not serve as permission boundaries. Workbook Folders (option c) do not exist as a native Tableau Server concept for permission isolation. Separate Tableau Desktop installations (option d) are client-side tools and have no bearing on server-side content organization.$patch$, $patch$Publish and Manage Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/server/en-us/projects.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Use Projects to Manage Content Access"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
