         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"IF/THEN/ELSE"},{"id":"b","text":"IIF"},{"id":"c","text":"CASE/WHEN"},{"id":"d","text":"FIXED LOD"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The expression uses CASE [field] WHEN [value] THEN [result] ... ELSE [default] END syntax, which is the CASE/WHEN logical construct in Tableau. IF/THEN/ELSE uses boolean conditions rather than value matching, IIF is an inline two-outcome conditional, and FIXED LOD is a level-of-detail expression, not a conditional branch. The source lists 'CASE/WHEN' under calculated field syntax.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
