INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau Desktop analyst connects to a large SQL Server database containing millions of rows. After noticing slow dashboard performance, the analyst wants to store a snapshot of the data locally for faster querying. Which connection type should the analyst configure?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Live connection"},{"id":"b","text":"Extract connection"},{"id":"c","text":"Published data source connection"},{"id":"d","text":"Web data connector"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$An Extract connection creates a local .hyper file snapshot of the data, enabling faster query performance by eliminating round-trips to the source database. A Live connection queries the source in real time and does not improve performance for large datasets. A Published data source connection simply references a data source already published to Tableau Server/Cloud. A Web data connector is used to pull data from web APIs, not for performance optimization of existing database connections.$patch$, $patch$Connect to and Transform Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/extracting_data.htm","label":"Tableau - Extract Your Data"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
