  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An analyst wants to understand how individual customer sales compare to the cohort average for their respective segment. Which type of table calculation should they use?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Percent of Total computed using Table (Down)"},{"id":"b","text":"Difference From computed using Pane (Down)"},{"id":"c","text":"Percent Difference From computed using Table (Across)"},{"id":"d","text":"Moving Average computed using Table (Down)"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Difference From computed at the Pane (Down) level calculates each customer's sales minus the average of all customers within the same segment pane, providing a direct comparison of each individual to their cohort. Percent of Total (a) shows each customer's share of the total, not a comparison to the average. Percent Difference From (c) using Table (Across) computes differences across columns, not within segments. Moving Average (d) computes a rolling average over sequential values, not a cohort comparison.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/calculations_tablecalculations.htm","label":"Tableau – Table Calculations"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
