         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"RANK(SUM([Sales])) with addressing set to Table (Down) and partitioning set to Region"},{"id":"b","text":"INDEX() computed within Region"},{"id":"c","text":"RANK(SUM([Sales])) with addressing set to Pane (Down) and partitioning set to Region"},{"id":"d","text":"RANK_UNIQUE(SUM([Sales])) with addressing set to Table (Across)"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$RANK(SUM([Sales])) with addressing Table (Down) and partitioning by Region will compute the rank within each Region partition separately, restarting for each region. This is the standard approach for within-group ranking. INDEX() (b) returns a sequential index, not a ranked value based on measure. Pane (Down) (c) is a valid addressing scope but refers to the visual pane in the view, which is not always synonymous with the Region partition. RANK_UNIQUE with Table (Across) (d) would rank across columns and not reset per region.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/functions_functions_tablecalculation.htm","label":"Tableau – RANK Function"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
