         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Parameter with a calculated field that references the parameter value"},{"id":"b","text":"Measure Names and Measure Values fields placed on Rows and Text"},{"id":"c","text":"A dashboard filter action targeting different sheets"},{"id":"d","text":"A sets action applied to a dimension field"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Using a Parameter combined with a calculated field (e.g., IF [Select Measure] = 'Sales' THEN [Sales] ELSEIF [Select Measure] = 'Profit' THEN [Profit] END) allows users to dynamically swap what measure is being visualized in a single view. Measure Names/Values (b) display multiple measures simultaneously rather than swapping between them. Dashboard filter actions (c) filter existing data but do not swap measures. Set actions (d) modify set membership, not the measure displayed.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/parameters_create.htm","label":"Tableau – Create Parameters"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
