         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Gantt chart"},{"id":"b","text":"Box-and-whisker plot"},{"id":"c","text":"Bullet chart"},{"id":"d","text":"Waterfall chart"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A box-and-whisker plot (box plot) is specifically designed to display the five-number summary (minimum, Q1, median, Q3, maximum) and show outliers as individual marks beyond the whiskers. It is the most appropriate chart type for identifying outliers in a distribution. A Gantt chart (a) is used for time-based task durations. A bullet chart (c) compares a measure to a target. A waterfall chart (d) shows cumulative effects of sequential values.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
