         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The calculation is performed only within each individual mark's row"},{"id":"b","text":"The calculation aggregates values across all columns within each row partition of the view"},{"id":"c","text":"The calculation aggregates values from the first row to the last row in the entire table"},{"id":"d","text":"The calculation resets at each pane boundary when dimensions are on both rows and columns"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Table (Across) means the calculation is computed horizontally — it addresses all marks across the columns within each row partition. So WINDOW_SUM(SUM([Sales])) computed Table (Across) would sum all column values for each row. Option (a) describes a per-mark computation, not a windowed one. Option (c) describes Table (Down) behavior. Option (d) describes Pane scope, not Table (Across).$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
