         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Trend Line with polynomial model"},{"id":"b","text":"Reference Band between two constant lines"},{"id":"c","text":"Average Line scoped to the entire table"},{"id":"d","text":"Moving Average from the Analytics pane dragged onto the view"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["d"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The Moving Average option in the Analytics pane allows the analyst to specify a window (e.g., 3 periods previous, 0 next) to compute a rolling average over time, smoothing short-term fluctuations. A trend line (a) fits a statistical model to all data points but does not compute a rolling window average. A reference band (b) shows a static range, not a rolling calculation. An average line (c) shows a single overall average, not a moving window.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
