  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$When would a Tableau analyst choose an INCLUDE LOD expression over a FIXED LOD expression?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"When they need the LOD calculation to respect all dimension filters in the view"},{"id":"b","text":"When they need the calculation to be computed at a finer grain than the view level of detail"},{"id":"c","text":"When they want the calculation to be computed at a coarser grain than the view level of detail"},{"id":"d","text":"When they want the calculation to ignore all context filters"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$INCLUDE LOD expressions add more dimensions to the computation beyond those in the current view, resulting in a finer grain of detail. For example, { INCLUDE [Order ID] : SUM([Sales]) } computes sales at the Order ID level even if the view is aggregated at a higher level. FIXED LODs (a) ignore dimension filters unless promoted to context. EXCLUDE LODs (c) compute at a coarser grain by removing dimensions. Option (d) describes FIXED behavior, not INCLUDE.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/calculations_calculatedfields_lod.htm","label":"Tableau – Level of Detail Expressions"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
