         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"DATEADD('day', [Order Date], [Ship Date])"},{"id":"b","text":"DATEPART('day', [Ship Date])"},{"id":"c","text":"DATEDIFF('day', [Order Date], [Ship Date])"},{"id":"d","text":"DATETRUNC('day', [Ship Date])"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$DATEDIFF(date_part, start_date, end_date) returns the difference between two dates in the specified unit. DATEADD adds an interval to a date, DATEPART extracts a part from a single date, and DATETRUNC truncates a date to the specified precision. The source material explicitly lists DATEDIFF under date functions.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/functions_functions_date.htm","label":"Tableau Date Functions"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
