  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau developer wants to compute the total sales per customer regardless of what dimensions are currently in the view. Which LOD expression type achieves this?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"{ INCLUDE [Customer] : SUM([Sales]) }"},{"id":"b","text":"{ EXCLUDE [Customer] : SUM([Sales]) }"},{"id":"c","text":"{ FIXED [Customer] : SUM([Sales]) }"},{"id":"d","text":"WINDOW_SUM(SUM([Sales]))"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$FIXED LOD expressions compute at the specified dimension level regardless of what is in the view. INCLUDE adds a dimension to the current view context, EXCLUDE removes one, and WINDOW_SUM is a table calculation, not an LOD. The source states: '{ FIXED [dim] : aggregate(measure) } — compute at the dim level regardless of view.'$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/calculations_calculatedfields_lod.htm","label":"Tableau LOD Expressions"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
