         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"File > Export As Version"},{"id":"b","text":"Server > Publish Workbook"},{"id":"c","text":"File > Save to Tableau Public"},{"id":"d","text":"Dashboard > Share"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$In Tableau Desktop, the 'Server > Publish Workbook' menu option initiates the workflow to publish a workbook to Tableau Server or Tableau Cloud. 'File > Export As Version' saves a copy in an older .twbx format locally. 'File > Save to Tableau Public' publishes to the public Tableau Public site, not a private Tableau Cloud site. 'Dashboard > Share' does not exist as a publishing mechanism in Tableau Desktop.$patch$, $patch$Publish and Manage Content$patch$,
