  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau Cloud site administrator wants to control how often a published extract data source is refreshed automatically. Where in Tableau Cloud would the administrator configure this schedule?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Content > Data Sources > select the data source > Refresh Extracts tab"},{"id":"b","text":"Settings > General > Extract Refresh"},{"id":"c","text":"Explore > All Projects > Data Alerts"},{"id":"d","text":"Tableau Desktop > Data > Refresh All Extracts"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$In Tableau Cloud, extract refresh schedules for a specific data source are managed by navigating to Content > Data Sources, selecting the data source, and using the 'Refresh Extracts' tab to add, edit, or remove schedules. The Settings > General page controls site-level settings but not per-source schedules. Data Alerts are notifications based on threshold conditions, not refresh schedules. Tableau Desktop's 'Refresh All Extracts' refreshes locally, not on the server.$patch$, $patch$Publish and Manage Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/online/en-us/extract_refresh.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Schedule Extract Refreshes on Tableau Cloud"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
