  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A data steward needs to allow a group of business users to access a published data source so they can build their own workbooks in Tableau Cloud without being able to edit or delete the data source itself. Which permission capability should be granted to the group on the published data source?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Write"},{"id":"b","text":"Connect"},{"id":"c","text":"Download Full Data"},{"id":"d","text":"Move"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The 'Connect' capability on a published data source allows users to connect to and use the data source when building or viewing content, without granting them the ability to edit, overwrite, or delete it. 'Write' would allow modifying the data source. 'Download Full Data' allows exporting underlying data rows. 'Move' allows relocating the data source to another project, which requires more than view-level access.$patch$, $patch$Publish and Manage Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/server/en-us/permissions_capabilities.htm#data-sources","label":"Tableau Help – Permissions Reference (Data Sources)"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
