  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau author publishes a workbook and wants viewers to be able to subscribe to a sheet so they receive a scheduled PNG snapshot via email. Which two site-level configurations must already be enabled by the site administrator for subscriptions to function? (Choose the single best answer that lists both correctly.)$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"SMTP email settings configured and the Subscriptions feature enabled on the site."},{"id":"b","text":"Row-Level Security enabled and Subscriptions feature enabled on the site."},{"id":"c","text":"SMTP email settings configured and Extract Refresh scheduling enabled."},{"id":"d","text":"Guest user access enabled and SMTP email settings configured."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$For subscriptions to work in Tableau Server or Tableau Cloud, the administrator must have configured SMTP mail server settings so the system can send emails, and the Subscriptions feature must be turned on at the site level. Row-Level Security, extract scheduling, and guest access are unrelated prerequisites for subscriptions. Without SMTP configuration there is no delivery mechanism, and without the feature being enabled users will not see the subscribe option.$patch$, $patch$Publish and Manage Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/server/en-us/subscribe.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Set Up a Site for Subscriptions"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
