         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Bar chart"},{"id":"b","text":"Bullet chart"},{"id":"c","text":"Box plot"},{"id":"d","text":"Waterfall chart"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material explicitly states that a Bullet chart is used for 'actual vs target with reference bands.' A bar chart compares categorical values but does not natively encode a target line with reference bands. A box plot shows distribution with quartiles and outliers. A waterfall chart shows cumulative additions/subtractions. Only the bullet chart is designed for the actual-vs-target-with-bands use case.$patch$, $patch$Create Content$patch$,
