  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An analyst needs to identify the top 10 customers by revenue. Which Tableau feature should they use to dynamically filter the view to only those customers?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"A Group containing the top 10 customer names"},{"id":"b","text":"A Set using a Top N condition based on SUM([Revenue])"},{"id":"c","text":"A FIXED LOD that ranks customers"},{"id":"d","text":"A Context Filter on [Customer Name]"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Sets support dynamic Top N conditions based on an aggregate measure, making them ideal for identifying the top 10 customers by revenue. Groups are static and require manual selection. A FIXED LOD can compute rank but doesn't natively filter. A Context Filter alone cannot define Top N logic. The source notes: 'Sets: dynamic OR static collection of dimension members; can use conditions or top N.'$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/sortgroup_sets_create.htm","label":"Tableau Sets"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
