         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The Top N filter itself"},{"id":"b","text":"A measure filter applied after the Top N"},{"id":"c","text":"The dimension filter used to restrict the data subset"},{"id":"d","text":"The date filter for the entire view"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A dimension filter that restricts the data (e.g., filtering to a specific region) should be made a Context Filter so that the Top N filter operates only on the already-filtered subset. Without this, the Top N would compute across all data first, then dimension filters would apply, potentially giving misleading results. The source states context filters 'become context for other filters' and appear earlier in the order of operations.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
