INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau analyst connects to a Microsoft Excel workbook that contains three sheets: Sales, Returns, and Targets. After connecting, the analyst notices that the Returns sheet is missing from the data source pane. What is the MOST likely reason for this?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The Returns sheet is hidden in the Excel workbook."},{"id":"b","text":"The Returns sheet has no numeric columns, so Tableau ignores it automatically."},{"id":"c","text":"Tableau only supports connecting to the first sheet in an Excel workbook."},{"id":"d","text":"The Returns sheet name contains a space, which Tableau cannot parse."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Tableau does not display hidden sheets from Excel workbooks in the data source pane. When a sheet is hidden in Excel, Tableau treats it as non-accessible by default. The other options are incorrect: Tableau does not require numeric columns to recognize a sheet, it supports multiple sheets, and sheet names with spaces are handled without issue.$patch$, $patch$Connect to and Transform Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/examples_excel.htm","label":"Tableau – Connect to Microsoft Excel"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
