INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An analyst creates a Tableau extract from a large database table containing 50 million rows. To reduce extract size and improve performance, the analyst wants to include only rows where the 'Region' field equals 'North America'. Where should this filter be configured?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"As a context filter on the worksheet."},{"id":"b","text":"As an extract filter before creating the .hyper file."},{"id":"c","text":"As a table calculation filter after aggregation."},{"id":"d","text":"As a measure filter on the Filters shelf."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$An extract filter is applied during extract creation and limits which rows are written into the .hyper file, directly reducing extract size and improving refresh and query performance. A context filter on a worksheet does not reduce the extract size; it only temporarily scopes other filters. Table calculation filters operate after aggregation and do not affect the extract. A measure filter on the Filters shelf also does not reduce the underlying extract data.$patch$, $patch$Connect to and Transform Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/extracting_data.htm","label":"Tableau – Extract Your Data"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
