INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau analyst is working with a published data source on Tableau Server. They need to add a new calculated field to the data source without affecting other workbooks that use it. What is the BEST approach?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Edit the published data source directly on Tableau Server and add the calculated field."},{"id":"b","text":"Create the calculated field in a local copy of the workbook without modifying the published data source."},{"id":"c","text":"Download the published data source, add the calculated field, and republish it, overwriting the original."},{"id":"d","text":"Use Tableau Prep Builder to modify the published data source schema."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Creating the calculated field locally within the workbook's connection to the published data source keeps the change isolated to that workbook, leaving the published data source and all other dependent workbooks unaffected. Editing or republishing the shared published data source would affect all workbooks connected to it. Tableau Prep Builder is used for data preparation flows, not for editing published data source schemas directly.$patch$, $patch$Connect to and Transform Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/publish_datasources_about.htm","label":"Tableau – Published Data Sources"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
