         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"FIXED"},{"id":"b","text":"EXCLUDE"},{"id":"c","text":"INCLUDE"},{"id":"d","text":"CONTEXT"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$INCLUDE adds the specified dimension into the calculation even if that dimension is not in the view, computing the aggregate at a finer granularity. FIXED computes at a specific level regardless of the view. EXCLUDE removes a dimension from the computation, producing a coarser level of detail. CONTEXT is a filter type, not an LOD keyword. The source states: 'INCLUDE [dim] : aggregate(measure) — add the dim into the calculation.'$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
