         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"By right-clicking the trend line and selecting 'Describe Trend Model'"},{"id":"b","text":"By opening the Analytics pane and clicking 'Model Statistics'"},{"id":"c","text":"By navigating to Analysis > Calculated Field"},{"id":"d","text":"By hovering over the trend line tooltip only; they cannot be shown elsewhere"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$In Tableau, right-clicking a trend line reveals the option 'Describe Trend Model', which opens a dialog showing model type, formula, R², and p-value. The Analytics pane does not have a 'Model Statistics' button. Calculated fields are unrelated to trend line statistics. Tooltip shows a summary but 'Describe Trend Model' is the dedicated way to access full statistics. The source notes: 'Trend Line (linear, logarithmic, exponential, polynomial, power) with R² and p-value.'$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
