  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau calculated field uses the expression: IF ISNULL([Discount]) THEN 0 ELSE [Discount] END. Which built-in function could replace this entire expression with a single function call?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"IFNULL([Discount], 0)"},{"id":"b","text":"IIF(ISNULL([Discount]), 0, [Discount])"},{"id":"c","text":"ZN([Discount])"},{"id":"d","text":"NULLIF([Discount], 0)"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$ZN(expression) returns the expression value if it is not null, and returns zero if it is null — exactly equivalent to IF ISNULL([Discount]) THEN 0 ELSE [Discount] END. IFNULL is also valid but the question asks for a single function that is the most concise and idiomatic replacement; ZN is specifically designed for this zero-null substitution pattern. IIF with ISNULL is functionally equivalent but uses two functions. NULLIF is not a standard Tableau function. The source lists: 'Logical: AND, OR, NOT, ISNULL, IFNULL, ZN.'$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/functions_functions_logical.htm","label":"Tableau Logical Functions"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
