         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Add [Sub-Category] to the FIXED expression's dimension list"},{"id":"b","text":"Convert the [Sub-Category] filter to a Context filter"},{"id":"c","text":"Change the LOD type from FIXED to INCLUDE"},{"id":"d","text":"Place the LOD expression on the Filters shelf as a Measure filter"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$In Tableau's order of operations, FIXED LODs are evaluated after Context filters but before Dimension filters. This means a standard Dimension filter on [Sub-Category] does not affect the FIXED LOD. By promoting the [Sub-Category] filter to a Context filter, it moves earlier in the pipeline — before FIXED LODs — so the FIXED LOD will then compute only over the filtered data. The source states: 'Context filters: become context for other filters and FIXED LODs' and the order is 'Context filters → FIXED LODs → Dimension filters.'$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
