INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A development team wants to embed a Tableau Cloud dashboard into a customer-facing web application and allow authenticated customers to view the dashboard without requiring each customer to have a Tableau license. The solution must support secure, programmatic authentication. Which approach aligns with Tableau's recommended embedded authentication method?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Embed the dashboard in an iframe using only the public share URL with no additional authentication."},{"id":"b","text":"Use Connected Apps with JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication together with the Tableau Embedding API v3."},{"id":"c","text":"Provide each customer with a Viewer site role account and embed the login form inside the iframe."},{"id":"d","text":"Use Tableau Bridge to proxy the embedded requests through the on-premises network."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states: 'Connected apps / JWT auth for embedded viewing' and references 'Tableau Embedding API v3 for programmatic interaction.' This combination allows a server-side application to generate a signed JWT token, which authenticates the embedded viewer without requiring each end user to hold a Tableau license (using Embedded Analytics / viewer tokens). Using a plain public share URL provides no access control. Giving each customer a Viewer account is impractical and costly at scale. Tableau Bridge is for keeping Tableau Cloud connected to on-premises data sources, not for embedding authentication.$patch$, $patch$Publish and Manage Content$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/online/en-us/connected_apps.htm","label":"Connected Apps — Tableau Help"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/api/embedding_api/en-us/index.html","label":"Tableau Embedding API v3 Overview"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'TDA-C01-P6'
