  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A folder contains 36 monthly CSV files named 'revenue_Jan_2021.csv' through 'revenue_Dec_2023.csv'. An analyst wants Tableau to automatically include all matching files as new months are added. Which connection approach is most efficient?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Manual union selecting each file individually"},{"id":"b","text":"Wildcard union using a pattern that matches the file naming convention"},{"id":"c","text":"Data blending with the folder as the secondary source"},{"id":"d","text":"Creating a separate data source for each file and using relationships"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A Wildcard Union allows Tableau to automatically include all files that match a specified naming pattern within a directory. When new files are added that match the pattern, they are incorporated automatically without manual intervention. The source material describes: 'wildcard union for files matching a pattern.' A manual union requires selecting each file explicitly and would not automatically pick up new months. Data blending and separate data sources with relationships are far more cumbersome approaches.$patch$, $patch$Connect to and Transform Data$patch$,
