         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"It is a continuous measure producing an axis."},{"id":"b","text":"It is a discrete dimension producing headers."},{"id":"c","text":"It is a geographic role field on an axis."},{"id":"d","text":"It is a Boolean field being aggregated."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Blue pills represent discrete fields in Tableau. When a discrete field is placed on a shelf it creates headers (column or row labels) rather than a continuous axis. The source material explains: 'Discrete (blue): affects axis type (continuous = axis, discrete = headers).' Order Date as a blue pill is being treated as a discrete dimension. A continuous field (green pill) would produce a numeric or date axis.$patch$, $patch$Connect to and Transform Data$patch$,
