         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Only orders that have a matching return record are included."},{"id":"b","text":"All orders are included; return data is null for orders with no match."},{"id":"c","text":"All returns are included; order data is null for returns with no match."},{"id":"d","text":"All rows from both tables are included regardless of matching keys."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A Left Join keeps every row from the left table (Orders) and includes matching rows from the right table (Returns). When no match exists in the right table, the right-side fields are null. The source material lists join types: 'Inner, Left, Right, Full Outer.' Only an Inner join would restrict to matched rows only (option A). A Right join would keep all returns (option C). A Full Outer join keeps all rows from both tables (option D).$patch$, $patch$Connect to and Transform Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/joining_tables.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Join Your Data"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
