         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The field is permanently deleted from the data source."},{"id":"b","text":"The field changes from a quantitative role used for aggregation to a qualitative role used for categorization, and its pill turns blue."},{"id":"c","text":"The field is converted to a date data type."},{"id":"d","text":"The field's aggregation is locked to COUNT."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Converting a measure to a dimension changes its role from quantitative (aggregated, green) to qualitative (categorical, blue). Dimensions are not aggregated by default and are used to slice and categorize data. The source material explains: 'Dimensions (qualitative, blue pill): typically discrete; categories, dates as discrete.' and 'Convert dimension <-> measure, continuous <-> discrete on demand.' The data type does not change, the field is not deleted, and the aggregation is not locked.$patch$, $patch$Connect to and Transform Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/datafields_changedatatype.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Change the Default Field Behavior"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
