  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A calculated field must return 'High' when Sales exceed 10000, 'Medium' when Sales exceed 5000, and 'Low' otherwise. Which Tableau syntax correctly implements this logic?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"CASE [Sales] WHEN 10000 THEN 'High' WHEN 5000 THEN 'Medium' ELSE 'Low' END"},{"id":"b","text":"IF [Sales] > 10000 THEN 'High' ELSEIF [Sales] > 5000 THEN 'Medium' ELSE 'Low' END"},{"id":"c","text":"IF [Sales] > 10000 THEN 'High' ELSE IF [Sales] > 5000 THEN 'Medium' END"},{"id":"d","text":"IIF([Sales] > 10000, 'High', IIF([Sales] > 5000, 'Medium'))"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The IF/THEN/ELSEIF/ELSE/END syntax in Tableau allows evaluation of a range of conditions. Option B correctly uses ELSEIF and closes with ELSE and END. Option A uses CASE/WHEN which performs equality checks and cannot evaluate range conditions like >10000. Option C uses incorrect nesting without a closing END for the outer IF. Option D's IIF requires a third argument for the else case and is missing it. The source material explicitly lists IF/THEN/ELSE/CASE/WHEN syntax under Calculated fields.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/functions_functions_logical.htm","label":"Tableau – IF Logical Functions"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
