  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An analyst applies a FIXED LOD expression: { FIXED [Region] : SUM([Sales]) }. At what stage does this LOD expression get evaluated relative to other filters in Tableau's order of operations?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"After dimension filters and before measure filters"},{"id":"b","text":"After context filters and before dimension filters"},{"id":"c","text":"After measure filters and before table calculations"},{"id":"d","text":"After data source filters and before context filters"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$According to the source material, the order of operations is: Extract filters → Data source filters → Context filters → FIXED LODs → Dimension filters → INCLUDE/EXCLUDE → Measure filters → Table calculations. FIXED LOD expressions are computed after context filters but before dimension filters. This means a dimension filter CAN filter out data that a FIXED LOD already aggregated, but a context filter will restrict the data seen by a FIXED LOD. Options A, C, and D all place FIXED LODs in incorrect positions within the order of operations.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/order_of_operations.htm","label":"Tableau – Order of Operations (Order of Filters)"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
