  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau analyst creates a set based on the top 10 customers by Sales. A user later changes a filter and new customers enter the top 10. How will the set behave?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The set will remain static and continue to show only the original top 10 customers."},{"id":"b","text":"The set will dynamically update to reflect the new top 10 customers based on the current data in the view."},{"id":"c","text":"The set will prompt the user to manually refresh its members."},{"id":"d","text":"The set will convert to a group and lock its members permanently."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$According to the source material, Sets can be dynamic — they can use conditions or top N criteria and will update based on the data currently in scope. When a filter changes the underlying data, a dynamic set defined by a Top N condition recalculates its membership. Static groups, by contrast, have fixed membership. The source material distinguishes between 'Groups (static)' and 'Sets (dynamic, with conditions or top N)'.$patch$, $patch$Explore and Analyze Data$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/sortgroup_sets_create.htm","label":"Tableau – Create Sets"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
